knowledge-path-ash-s1-name = Nightwatcher's Secret
knowledge-path-ash-s1-desc =
    Opens up the Path of Ash to you.
    Allows you to transmute a welding tool and a knife into an Ashen Blade.
    ---

    The City Guard know their watch. If you ask them at night, they may tell you about the ashy lantern.

knowledge-path-ash-s2-name = Grasp of Ash
knowledge-path-ash-s2-desc =
    Your Mansus Grasp will burn the eyes of the victim, blurring their vision.
    ---

    The Nightwatcher remains. Her love started it all. Their lantern, expired to ash - their watch, absent.

knowledge-path-ash-s3-name = Blazing Dash
knowledge-path-ash-s3-desc =
    Grants you Blazing Dash, a spell that lets you move extremely quickly for a short time, while setting you ablaze. Be sure to bring a firesuit.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
    ---

    Her formulae thrust man from the slow clinks of flint to the blazing fires of industry.

knowledge-path-ash-s4-name = Mark of Ash
knowledge-path-ash-s4-desc =
    Your Mansus Grasp now applies the Mark of Ash. The mark is triggered from an attack with your Ashen Blade.
    When triggered, its target is set ablaze and takes a large amount of stamina damage, before jumping to a new target.
    ---

    She was a very particular woman, always working in the dead of night.
    But in spite of her duty, she regularly wandered through the Manse, hand-in-hand with the sky's blazing lantern.
    He shone brightly in the darkness, until the blaze begin to die.

knowledge-path-ash-s5-name = Volcanic Blast
knowledge-path-ash-s5-desc =
    Grants you Volcanic Blast, a spell that fires a ball of flame at the nearest heathen.
    Upon successfully hitting its target, the fireball divides into multiple smaller fireballs targeting other nearby heathens.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
    ---

    No fire was hot enough to rekindle her love. No fire was bright enough to save them. No fire is eternal.

knowledge-path-ash-s6-name = Mask of Madness
knowledge-path-ash-s6-desc =
    Allows you to transmute any mask, four candles, a stun baton, and a liver to create a Mask of Madness.
    The mask instills fear into heathens who witness it, causing stamina damage, hallucinations, and insanity.
    It cannot be taken off without outside help, for Heretic and heathen alike.
    ---

    The Watchman was lost. That's what the old watch believed. Yet he walked the world, split into parts.

knowledge-path-ash-s7-name = Fiery Blade
knowledge-path-ash-s7-desc =
    Your Ashen Blade now lights enemies aflame on attack.
    ---

    The Nightwatcher, alone in her wanderings, came across the last ashes of the Watchman.
    It was hot enough to burn worlds to ash, yet just right for her to drink deeply.

knowledge-path-ash-s8-name = Nightwatcher's Rebirth
knowledge-path-ash-s8-desc =
    Grants you Nightwatcher's Rebirth, a spell that extinguishes you and burns all nearby heathens who are currently on fire, healing you for every victim afflicted.
    If any victims afflicted are in critical condition, they will instantly die.
    This spell requires a Focus to cast.
    ---

    The two became one. The Forge became the Nightwatcher. She became He. The Seventh Sun was no more, and together the lovers became the Eighth.

knowledge-path-ash-s9-name = Ashlord's Rite
knowledge-path-ash-s9-desc =
    The Ascension ritual of the Path of Ash
    Bring 3 burning corpses to a Transmutation Rune to complete the ritual.
    When completed, you become a Harbinger of Flames, gaining a new ability, Oath of Flame, which sets you ablaze and causes you to passively create a ring of flames as you walk.
    You will also become immune to flames, space, and similar environmental hazards.
